REGULAR EXPRESSIONS:
    . : Any character.
    [abc]: Exactly given letters.
    [abc][def]: Either first or second set.
    [^abc]: Except abc.
    [a-z1-7]: a-z or 1-7.
    A | B : A or B.
    XZ : Exactly XZ.

    we use the method matches to perform validations.


META CHARACTERS:
    These are meant for symbols.
    \d : Digits.
    \D : Not Digit.
    \s : Space.
    \S : Not Space.
    \w : Alphabets or digits.
    \W : Neither alphabet nor digits.


QUANTIFIERS:
    * : 0 or more.
    + : one or more.
    ? : 0 or 1 time.
    {x} : x times.
    {x,y} : between x and y.




